      "content": "That seems like a very biased way to approach justice. If a judge is looking at \"lack of stable roots\" or \"failure to assimilate\" as indicators of poor character, aren't they essentially just using socioeconomic status and neighborhood as proxies for criminality? Even with no prior record, wouldn't that approach disproportionately target people of color who live in these urban areas?",
